de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util

Class RecursiveEvaluableExpressionVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util.ExpressionTreeWalker
      • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util.PartialExpressionTreeWalker
        • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util.RecursiveEvaluableExpressionVisitor

  • public abstract class RecursiveEvaluableExpressionVisitor
extends PartialExpressionTreeWalker
    Visitor of EvaluableExpressions, recursively visiting all their inner expressions.

    This visitor will start at the expression passed to visitRecursively(EvaluableExpression) and call the according at hook. Afterwards, it will recursively visit all inner expressions and then call the after hook. It thus realises a depth-first traversal of the tree formed by each expression. If PartialExpressionTreeWalker.stopTraversingInnerExpressions() is called, the traversal will no longer visit inner expressions. Instead, it will go “up” the tree again, whilst calling the after hooks, until it reached the initial expression and then terminate. Given that no exception is thrown, the traversal of one expression tree that only contains pairwise different inner expressions has these properties:

    • for each type, the number of called at hooks will equal the number of called after hooks.
    • if for two expression e1 and e2, atExpression(e1) was called before atExpression(e2) was, afterExpression(e2) will be called before afterExpression(e1) will be called.

    Please note that evaluable expressions may often contain an instance of one evaluable expression multiple times. For every new visit, traversing of inner expressions will be enabled.

    This visitor is not thread safe. It may only be used to traverse one expression at a time, meaning that its results are undefined if visitRecursively(EvaluableExpression) is called when getTraversalDepth() does not return -1. There is however no limitation on how many expression trees can be visited by an instance of this class.
